extremePOSMib.name: extremePOSMib
extremePOSMib.description: Extreme POS objects: objects common to POS MIBs

extremeApsGroupConfigTable.name: extremeApsGroupConfigTable
extremeApsGroupConfigTable.description: This table contains configuration information by defined APS group.

extremeApsGroupConfigGroupNumber.name: extremeApsGroupConfigGroupNumber
extremeApsGroupConfigGroupNumber.description: The group number which uniquely identifies the APS group.

extremeApsGroupConfigRevertMode.name: extremeApsGroupConfigRevertMode
extremeApsGroupConfigRevertMode.description: The revertive mode configured for the APS group. This indicates whether APS will switch-back automatically after the working line error is cleared. In non-revertive mode, manual intervention is required for switch-back.

extremeApsGroupConfigRevertMinutes.name: extremeApsGroupConfigRevertMinutes
extremeApsGroupConfigRevertMinutes.description: The number of minutes APS will wait after the error has been cleared before switching back to the working line. During this interval, the K1 request will indicate WTR (wait-to-restore). This field is only valid in revertive mode.

extremeApsGroupConfigDirection.name: extremeApsGroupConfigDirection
extremeApsGroupConfigDirection.description: The directional mode configured for the APS group. This indicates whether protection switches are coordinated between both POS equipment and ADM (bidirectional) or not (unidirectional).

extremeApsGroupConfigTimerInterval.name: extremeApsGroupConfigTimerInterval
extremeApsGroupConfigTimerInterval.description: The number of seconds between APS out-of-band peer protocol hello messages. This value is relevant when the working line and protection line exist is physically different chassis.

extremeApsGroupConfigTimerMisses.name: extremeApsGroupConfigTimerMisses
extremeApsGroupConfigTimerMisses.description: The number of APS out-of-band peer protocol messages transmitted without receiving a response before the protection switch declares the working switch inoperable. When this occurs the protection switch initiates a line switch over via APS.

extremeApsGroupConfigAuthenticate.name: extremeApsGroupConfigAuthenticate
extremeApsGroupConfigAuthenticate.description: When enabled, the authentication string on both working and protection switches must match.

extremeApsGroupConfigAuthString.name: extremeApsGroupConfigAuthString
extremeApsGroupConfigAuthString.description: If configured, this is the authentication string that must match between working and protection switches. This field is relevant if the APS group is configured to authenticate.

extremeApsPortConfigTable.name: extremeApsPortConfigTable
extremeApsPortConfigTable.description: This table contains configuration information for APS ports.

extremeApsPortConfigGroupNumber.name: extremeApsPortConfigGroupNumber
extremeApsPortConfigGroupNumber.description: The group number which uniquely identifies the APS group.

extremeApsPortConfigPortNumber.name: extremeApsPortConfigPortNumber
extremeApsPortConfigPortNumber.description: The value of ifIndex that identifies the port.

extremeApsProtectPortConfigTable.name: extremeApsProtectPortConfigTable
extremeApsProtectPortConfigTable.description: This table contains configuration information for APS protection ports.

extremeApsProtectPortConfigGroupNumber.name: extremeApsProtectPortConfigGroupNumber
extremeApsProtectPortConfigGroupNumber.description: The group number which uniquely identifies the APS group.

extremeApsProtectPortConfigPortNumber.name: extremeApsProtectPortConfigPortNumber
extremeApsProtectPortConfigPortNumber.description: The value of ifIndex that identifies the protection port.

extremeApsProtectPortConfigWorkingIpAddr.name: extremeApsProtectPortConfigWorkingIpAddr
extremeApsProtectPortConfigWorkingIpAddr.description: The IP address of the working switch. If the working and protection lines reside on the same chassis, this IP address will be a local address.

extremeApsGroupTable.name: extremeApsGroupTable
extremeApsGroupTable.description: This table contains run-time information by defined APS group.

extremeApsGroupGroupNumber.name: extremeApsGroupGroupNumber
extremeApsGroupGroupNumber.description: The group number which uniquely identifies the APS group.

extremeApsGroupActivePort.name: extremeApsGroupActivePort
extremeApsGroupActivePort.description: The APS port which is currently carrying the network traffic.

extremeApsGroupEffectiveDirection.name: extremeApsGroupEffectiveDirection
extremeApsGroupEffectiveDirection.description: The effective directional mode for the APS group. When this value differs from the configured directional mode, check the ADM and switch provisioning for a mis- configuration.

extremeApsGroupPeerProtoStatus.name: extremeApsGroupPeerProtoStatus
extremeApsGroupPeerProtoStatus.description: The APS out-of-band peer protocol status for a group.

extremeApsProtectPortTable.name: extremeApsProtectPortTable
extremeApsProtectPortTable.description: This table contains run-time information by defined APS protection port.

extremeApsProtectPortGroupNumber.name: extremeApsProtectPortGroupNumber
extremeApsProtectPortGroupNumber.description: The group number which uniquely identifies the APS group.

extremeApsProtectPortPortNumber.name: extremeApsProtectPortPortNumber
extremeApsProtectPortPortNumber.description: The value of ifIndex that identifies the protection port.

extremeApsProtectPortTransmitK1.name: extremeApsProtectPortTransmitK1
extremeApsProtectPortTransmitK1.description: The K1 overhead byte currently being transmitted on the indicated protection port.

extremeApsProtectPortTransmitK2.name: extremeApsProtectPortTransmitK2
extremeApsProtectPortTransmitK2.description: The K2 overhead byte currently being transmitted on the indicated protection port.

extremeApsProtectPortReceiveK1.name: extremeApsProtectPortReceiveK1
extremeApsProtectPortReceiveK1.description: The K1 overhead byte currently being received on the indicated protection port.

extremeApsProtectPortReceiveK2.name: extremeApsProtectPortReceiveK2
extremeApsProtectPortReceiveK2.description: The K2 overhead byte currently being received on the indicated protection port.

extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByWorking.name: extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByWorking
extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByWorking.description: The number of switches that have been initiated by the working-line router.

extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByProtect.name: extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByProtect
extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByProtect.description: The number of switches that have been initiated by the protection-line router.

extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByADM.name: extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByADM
extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByADM.description: The number of switches that have been initiated by the ADM.

extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByCmd.name: extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByCmd
extremeApsProtectPortSwitchInitByCmd.description: The number of switches that have been initiated by an external CLI command.

extremeApsProtectPortSuccessfulSwitches.name: extremeApsProtectPortSuccessfulSwitches
extremeApsProtectPortSuccessfulSwitches.description: The number of successful APS line switches.

extremeApsProtectPortHelloProtFails.name: extremeApsProtectPortHelloProtFails
extremeApsProtectPortHelloProtFails.description: The number of APS out-of-band peer protocol failures recorded. This situation causes the protection-line router to initiate a line switch.

extremeApsLineErrorTable.name: extremeApsLineErrorTable
extremeApsLineErrorTable.description: This table contains APS line error information.

extremeApsLineErrorGroupNumber.name: extremeApsLineErrorGroupNumber
extremeApsLineErrorGroupNumber.description: The group number which uniquely identifies the APS group.

extremeApsLineErrorPortNumber.name: extremeApsLineErrorPortNumber
extremeApsLineErrorPortNumber.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the APS port.

extremeApsLineErrorSignalDegradeActive.name: extremeApsLineErrorSignalDegradeActive
extremeApsLineErrorSignalDegradeActive.description: Indicates whether a signal degrade condition currently exists on the line.

extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalDegradeActiv.name: extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalDegradeActive
extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalDegradeActiv.description: Indicates whether a signal degrade condition due to excessive Bit-Error-Rate currently exists on the line.

extremeApsLineErrorSignalFailActive.name: extremeApsLineErrorSignalFailActive
extremeApsLineErrorSignalFailActive.description: Indicates whether a signal fail condition currently exists on the line.

extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalFailActive.name: extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalFailActive
extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalFailActive.description: Indicates whether a signal fail condition due to excessive Bit-Error-Rate currently exists on the line.

extremeApsLineErrorSignalDegrades.name: extremeApsLineErrorSignalDegrades
extremeApsLineErrorSignalDegrades.description: The number of signal degrades that have been recorded on the line.

extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalDegrades.name: extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalDegrades
extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalDegrades.description: The number of signal degrades due to excessive Bit-Error-Rate that have been recorded on the line.

extremeApsLineErrorSignalFails.name: extremeApsLineErrorSignalFails
extremeApsLineErrorSignalFails.description: The number of signal fails that have been recorded on the line.

extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalFails.name: extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalFails
extremeApsLineErrorBERSignalFails.description: The number of signal fails due to excessive Bit-Error-Rate that have been recorded on the line.

extremeApsProtocolErrorTable.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorTable
extremeApsProtocolErrorTable.description: This table contains APS protocol error information. These errors are relevant for APS protection ports.

extremeApsProtocolErrorGroupNumber.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorGroupNumber
extremeApsProtocolErrorGroupNumber.description: The group number which uniquely identifies the APS group.

extremeApsProtocolErrorPortNumber.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorPortNumber
extremeApsProtocolErrorPortNumber.description: The ifIndex value which identifies the APS protection port.

extremeApsProtocolErrorModeMismatchDefec.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorModeMismatchDefect
extremeApsProtocolErrorModeMismatchDefec.description: Indicates whether a Mode Mismatch defect currently exists on the port.

extremeApsProtocolErrorProtSwitchByteDef.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorProtSwitchByteDefect
extremeApsProtocolErrorProtSwitchByteDef.description: Indicates whether a Protection Switching Byte defect currently exists on the port.

extremeApsProtocolErrorChannelMismatchDe.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorChannelMismatchDefect
extremeApsProtocolErrorChannelMismatchDe.description: Indicates whether a Channel Mismatch defect currently exists on the port.

extremeApsProtocolErrorFarEndProtectDefe.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorFarEndProtectDefect
extremeApsProtocolErrorFarEndProtectDefe.description: Indicates whether a Far-End Protection defect currently exists on the port.

extremeApsProtocolErrorModeMismatchFailu.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorModeMismatchFailure
extremeApsProtocolErrorModeMismatchFailu.description: Indicates whether a Mode Mismatch failure currently exists on the port.

extremeApsProtocolErrorProtSwitchByteFai.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorProtSwitchByteFailure
extremeApsProtocolErrorProtSwitchByteFai.description: Indicates whether a Protection Switching Byte failure currently exists on the port.

extremeApsProtocolErrorChannelMismatchFa.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorChannelMismatchFailure
extremeApsProtocolErrorChannelMismatchFa.description: Indicates whether a Channel Mismatch failure currently exists on the port.

extremeApsProtocolErrorFarEndProtectFail.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorFarEndProtectFailure
extremeApsProtocolErrorFarEndProtectFail.description: Indicates whether a Far-End Protection failure currently exists on the port.

extremeApsProtocolErrorModeMismatchNumFa.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorModeMismatchNumFails
extremeApsProtocolErrorModeMismatchNumFa.description: The number of Mode Mismatch failures that have been recorded.

extremeApsProtocolErrorProtSwitchByteNum.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorProtSwitchByteNumFails
extremeApsProtocolErrorProtSwitchByteNum.description: The number of Protection Switching Byte failures that have been recorded.

extremeApsProtocolErrorChannelMismatchNu.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorChannelMismatchNumFails
extremeApsProtocolErrorChannelMismatchNu.description: The number of Channel Mismatch failures that have been recorded.

extremeApsProtocolErrorFarEndProtectNumF.name: extremeApsProtocolErrorFarEndProtectNumFails
extremeApsProtocolErrorFarEndProtectNumF.description: The number of Far-End Protection failures that have been recorded.
